This paper deals with unsupervised learning techniques in computer vision and pattern recognition, specifically subspace clustering and feature extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also makes use of recent advances in sparsity and rank minimization, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also introduces a numerical solver for the proposed framework, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) may be a relevant category. Additionally, the paper discusses the conditions under which the proposed framework can reveal true subspace memberships, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with unsupervised learning, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant category.
